Mysuru
City in Karnataka
Mysore (or Mysuru), a city in India's southwestern Karnataka state, was the capital of the Kingdom of Mysore from 1399 to 1947. In its center is opulent Mysore Palace, seat of the former ruling Wodeyar dynasty. The palace blends Hindu, Islamic, Gothic and Rajput styles. Mysore is also home to the centuries-old Devaraja Market, filled with spices, silk and sandalwood. ― Google
Elevation: 763 m
Area: 155 km²
District: Mysore district
Local time: Friday, 1:41 pm
Metro population: 9,90,900

Why the Mysore is famous?
Mysore is noted for its heritage structures and palaces, including the Mysore Palace, and for the festivities that take place during the Dasara festival when the city receives hundreds of thousands of tourists from around the world.
Which sweet is famous in Mysore?
Image result
Mysore and Bangalore - Halbai

Halbai is an exotic and a unique delicacy; its softy-slimy consistency makes it one of the unusual sweets. It is a famous sweet from the regions of Mysore and Bengaluru.
